                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18171203-157-defend1158 t18171203-157-deflabel856"></join>. On the 26th of November he went down stairs, pretending to go to the yard, and never returned. I missed the things.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18171203-157-person1162">
                  MARY 
                  RORK
               <interp inst="t18171203-157-person1162" type="surname" value="RORK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18171203-157-person1162" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18171203-157-person1162" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of the last witness. About half-past six o'clock the prisoner came down stairs, and went into the yard; he went through the room where the things were-he did not return - He must have got over the wall. I went out to seek him, about half-past nine, at the Two Brewers, public-house; he said he knew nothing of them. Nobody but himself could have been there. I saw them safe just before he left.</p>
